 <h3 class="title"><a href="node/2545#comment-38429" class="active">AST with types</a></h3>
 <div class="content"><p >The trees alone don't tell me much about type inference, but my teacher used to use them with associated types. My problem is that I have the finished tree with all the types in the right place, but I can't understand the process.<br >
I mean: where is the starting point?</p>
<p >Actually I have the same problem with the derivation in the natural deduction style. Does the inference starts from the top towards bottom or vice-versa? Or is it the same?</p></div>
